WARMBOOT

Syntax: warmboot
        warmboot loaded
        warmboot std
        warmboot <domain>
        warmboot all

Reloads LPC source from disk without restarting the driver or
dropping connections. Online admins are notified when a warmboot
starts and finishes. Logged to /log/adm/warmboot.

FORMS

  warmboot
    Ensures runtime save/log directories exist (including apprentice
    submission dirs), reloads every .c under /daemon/,
    /secure/daemon/, /cmds/, /secure/cmds/, /obj/, and
    /domains/adm/, then rehashes the command daemon.

  warmboot loaded
    Walks all objects currently in memory (via objects()) and
    recompiles each unique non-player program once.  Useful for
    refreshing cloned NPCs and rooms already instantiated.

  warmboot std
    Prompts for confirmation, then reloads all /std/ blueprints.
    Online players keep old inherited behavior until relog.

  warmboot <domain>
    Reloads all .c files under /domains/<domain>/ recursively.
    Tries exact, capitalized, and lower-case directory names.
    Example: warmboot tolkeen

  warmboot all
    Prompts for confirmation, then reloads all domains plus
    daemon, cmd, std, and obj trees.

MECHANISM

  Same as update: destruct existing blueprint (if any), then
  call_other(file, "???") to recompile from disk.

LIMITS (standard for LPC muds)

  - Player save files (/secure/save/users/) are never reloaded.
  - Connected player bodies do not pick up /std/ inheritance
    changes until relog or driver restart.
  - master.c and simul-efun changes require ./mud.sh stop/start.
  - For a single file: update /path/to/file
  Available to Admin wizards (position arch or head arch).

